  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up as you go</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-black-bean-rice/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>cumin</strong> and crumble in the <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, stirring well to combine</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>rice</strong> and stir to coat the grains</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;water and the drained <strong>black beans</strong> and bring to the boil covered with a lid over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-black-bean-rice/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low, cover with a lid and cook for 10-15 min or until the water has absorbed and the rice is tender</p>\r\n<p>Tip: add a splash or two of water if the rice looks too dry</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-black-bean-rice/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, quarter the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;(skin on) and discard the core<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\r\n<p>Chop into small, bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-black-bean-rice/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>spring onions</strong> finely, discarding the root ends</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-black-bean-rice/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-black-bean-rice/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is tender, fluff it with a fork and taste for seasoning, adding more<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p>\r\n<p>Remove the pan from the heat, then stir through the <strong>apple</strong>, <strong>spring onion</strong> and<strong> coriander</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-black-bean-rice/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the pork and black bean rice in bowls</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
